tradeAmendments.notes: The agreed-to version of this trade attached the following condition to the 3rd round draft pick: conditionally upgrades to a 2nd round draft pick should Patrick win a 2011 playoff game. Patrick lost in the semifinals so it remained a 3rd rounder.

The agreed-to version of this trade attached the following condition to the 4th round draft pick: conditionally upgrades to a 3rd round draft pick should John win a 2011 playoff game. John didn't make the playoffs so it remained a 4th rounder.

The agreed-to version of this trade attached the following condition to the 2nd round draft pick: conditionally downgrades to a 3rd round draft pick should Patrick win a 2011 playoff game. It also attached the following condition to the 3rd round draft pick: conditionally downgrades to a 4th round draft pick should John win a 2011 playoff game. Patrick lost in the semifinals and John didn't make the playoffs so the picks remained 2nd and 3rd rounders, respectively.
The origins of all four picks in this trade are self-explanatory: none of them had been traded until this deal was made.
Brett/Luke originally owned both RFA rights; Koci/Mueller originally owned the future 2nd and 3rd; Schex originally owned the 3.04 and 3.11.

The 2022 picks involved in this trade should not have been available to Quinn to trade in 2019. It was erroneously approved by the commissioner but not definitively ruled a mistake until it was seen as too late to roll back.
Schex originally owned both Khalil Herbert and Montrell Washington; Justin originally owned Dallas Goedert. Keyon did not give up an asset in this trade.

tradeCashCorrections.notes: The agreed-to version of this trade moved $15 from Schexes to Patrick in 2025. That transaction was never carried out on the spreadsheet, though, and the error was not noticed by anyone until over a year later.

The agreed-to version of this trade moved the $20 from Keyon to Mitch in 2025, not 2026. The transaction was incorrectly carried out on the spreadsheet and not noticed by anyone until nearly two years later.
